    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## AI Risk Evaluation\r\n\r\nSee how an AI system might assess risky behavior based on your user's login activity.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Load your user’s profile from the Library so the AI understands what’s normal for them. \r\n2. Type in the first of the four risk scenarios from your activity guide. \r\n3. Then, ask the AI to:\r\n   - Evaluate the risk and assign a risk score\r\n   - Choose the authentication method required based on that score\r\n   - Explain its reasoning using details from the scenario and user profile\r\n4. Repeat this process for the other three scenarios. \r\n\r\nCompare the AI’s responses to your own predictions. Record the risk level, authentication method, and explanation for each one in your activity guide.\r\n\r\n---\r\n**Try it out!** \r\n\r\n:::details [<i class=\"fa fa-briefcase\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Need a starting prompt?**]\r\n>Here’s a scenario for the user whose profile I loaded from the Library:\r\n[Type in your first scenario here.]\r\n\r\n>Based on this scenario, what is the risk score?\r\n\r\n>What type of authentication would be required, and why?\r\n:::\r\n&nbsp\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [<i class=\"fa fa-file-image-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **How do I add a user profile and audit logs?**]\r\n- Click the button labeled **Add** below your chat input.\r\n- Choose **From Library**\r\n- Then browse the existing files.\r\n- When you find your user's file to upload, click the checkbox next to it to select it and then click **Attach**.\r\n- You should see the file get added to the message being sent to AI Chat.\r\n:::\r\n",
